<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="283" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,438,151,211]" box="[151,255,186,211]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,246,186,211]" captionStart="FIGURES 1" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1932,1955]" captionTargetBox="[166,1431,213,1876]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,213,1876]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 1A–1F. Habitus of Agrilus. 1A, A. cameronius sp. nov., holotype (10.5 mm); 1B, A. indigaceus Deyrolle, 1864 (9.2 mm); 1C, A. morio Kerremans, 1895 (11.2 mm); 1D, A. puncak sp. nov. holotype (12 mm); 1E, A. purpurifrons Deyrolle, 1864 (9.7 mm); 1F, A. raapi Kerremans, 1900 (10.6 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2599438/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,253,1245]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,439,253,278]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">
Description of 
<typeStatus box="[330,435,253,278]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
Length: 
<quantity box="[543,627,254,278]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="4" pageNumber="283" unit="mm" value="12.0">12 mm</quantity>
. BODY. Shape: cuneiform; Build: robust; Color (dorsally): unicolored. HEAD. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[247,332,286,311]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Vertex.</emphasis>
Shape: flat; Medial impression: present; Sculpture elements: rugae; Sculpture aspect: arcuate; Sculpture intensity: rough. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[466,529,319,344]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Eyes.</emphasis>
Size: subequal or larger than width of vertex (dorsal view); Shape: markedly protruding head outline; Lower margin: in line or below antennal socket; Median orbit: converging ventrally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,253,1245]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,386,411]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Antennae.</emphasis>
Serration: from antennomere 4. PRONOTUM. Shape: visually transverse; Sides: markedly arcuate; Maximal width: at middle; Anterior margin: narrower than posterior. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[969,1142,420,445]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Anterior lobe.</emphasis>
Development: moderate; Shape: arcuate; Width: broad; Position: at level with anterior angles. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[918,1117,453,478]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Posterior angles.</emphasis>
Shape: obtuse; Apex: sharp.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,253,1245]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,212,486,511]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Disk.</emphasis>
Impressions: medial and lateral; Medial impression: anteromedial and posteromedial; Lateral impressions (width): broad. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[336,491,519,544]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Prehumerus.</emphasis>
Development: carinal; Shape: bisinuate; Extent: beyond 1/2 of pronotal length; Anterior end: joined with lateral pronotal carina; Posterior end: distant from posterior pronotal angle or margin; Arc: obvious. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[309,501,586,611]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Lateral carinae.</emphasis>
Convergence: moderate; Junction: present; Narrowest point: at posterior 1/5–1/4 of marginal carina; Modifications: submarginal carina anteriorly obliterate. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[986,1113,620,645]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Scutellum.</emphasis>
Disc: impressed. ELYTRA. Humeral carina: absent. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[427,513,653,678]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Apices.</emphasis>
Arrangement: separate; Shape: cuspidate; Number of cusps or spines: 1; Position of dominant projection: pleural margin. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[656,793,686,711]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Tomentum.</emphasis>
Pairs of tomentose spots: humeral, medial, apical. STERNUM. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[302,496,719,744]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Prosternal lobe.</emphasis>
Size: large; Distal margin: arcuately emarginate; Emargination (depth): shallow; Emargination (width): wide. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[477,705,753,778]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Prosternal process.</emphasis>
Shape: markedly dilated; Sides: arcuate; Angles: obtuse; Angles (tips): blunt; Disc: flat; Projection (length): protruding distinctly beyond angles. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1121,1290,786,811]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Metasternum.</emphasis>
Metasternal projection: flat. ABDOMEN. Tomentum: present. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[734,856,820,845]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Pygidium.</emphasis>
Apical margin: with spine. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1186,1349,820,845]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Last ventrite.</emphasis>
Shape: with narrow apex. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[382,569,853,878]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Sternal groove.</emphasis>
Shape on apex of last ventrite: arcuate. LEGS. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1164,1307,853,878]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Metatarsus.</emphasis>
Length to metatibia: distinctly shorter. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[485,700,886,911]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Metatarsomere 1.</emphasis>
Length to following tarsomeres: subequal or longer than 2–4. GENITALIA. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[313,446,919,944]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Ovipositor.</emphasis>
Shape: markedly elongate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,253,1245]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,333,953,978]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Variability.</emphasis>
Body length: 
<quantity box="[522,698,954,978]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.18" metricValueMax="1.28" metricValueMin="1.08" pageId="4" pageNumber="283" unit="mm" value="11.8" valueMax="12.8" valueMin="10.8">10.8–12.8 mm</quantity>
. Without discernible variability except for the size. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Sexual dimorphism.</emphasis>
The species is known only from females.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
